Tested on Godot 2.1, Windows 10 64 bits

After [making a mistake](https://github.com/godotengine/godot/issues/7738) in parsing a JSON file (using get_line instead of get_as_text), I realized Godot doesn't return an error code when the data is only made of a `{`. It's actually invalid JSON.

Repro code:
```gdscript
func _ready():
	var data_dict = {}
	var ret = data_dict.parse_json("{")
	if ret != 0:
		print("ERROR: cannot parse save file, error code: " + str(ret))
	else:
		print("No problem")
```
Prints "No problem", it should return a non-zero error instead (`[` returns an error).

#FoundAtGodotCon
